Czech Republic has the chance to reach 365 billion
Czech ministers and representatives of the European Commission signed a total of nine development programmes yesterday, which will enable the Czech Republic to reach 14 billion euros (about 365 billion kroner) in the coming years.
It is about half of the sum that the Czech Republic will be able to receive from Brussels in the years 2007 to 2013.
About 125 billion crowns come from seven regional development programmes.
Czech companies will be able to receive around 100 billion crowns from the "Company and Innovation" programme.
Most of the money, about 150 billion, will flow into traffic expansion.
The Transport Programme is the largest development programme and covers up to 22 percent of the funds that the Czech Republic can obtain from the Fund.
This money increases according to the budget of the State Transport Infrastructure Fund, which will have 90.8 billion next year.
The "Company and innovation" programme is intended to help entrepreneurs and companies to attract funds to innovative enterprises.
The aim is for companies to gain finance for the introduction of new technologies, for business research, but also for the introduction of more effective organizational methods.
The Czech Republic is one of the least successful candidate countries to date in the current money acquisition from EU funds.
