60000 people failed to exchange their driver's license
60000 drivers missed the deadline to exchange their old driving licence, which expires at the end of the year.
Today is the last day where you can apply for the exchange, so that the authorities manage to issue a new driving licence by the end of the year.
However, the Ministry does not fear that after New Year's Eve hundreds of thousands of drivers will be on the roads without a valid driving licence.
According to the authorities, mainly those who do not want to drive have not exchanged their driving license.
While small places report a sharp decline in interest in the early exchange, the capital's offices are covered with applications, and the interest in exchange grew this week.
The city administration manufactures around 2000 customers a day.
You have to wait about half an hour.
In Prague, about 140000 drivers have not yet exchanged their driver's license.
The exhibition of a new driving license lasts 20 days.
But it is possible to apply for the exhibition with a shortened period of five days.
In this case, however, the driver must add 500 crowns.
Drivers who fail to make the required exchange by the end of the year and leave without a valid driver's license will face a fine from January.
The culprit pays a maximum of 2,000 crowns.
However, the police can also use a reminder in the case of transgression.
In the event of an infringement, the penalty may rise to 2500 crowns.
According to previous information, even those who do not drive can be punished by the community.
He could, it was said, face a penalty of even 30000 crowns.
The ministry already called on the offices to exercise mildness and to impose a maximum penalty of 1000 crowns.
According to the spokesman for the Ministry of Transport, Karel Hanzelka, no one threatened a thousand crown penalty.
The driving licence is a document in which everyone can decide whether to own it or not.
It is not an identity card that everyone, and a valid one, must have.
People who don't want to drive should give up their driver's license.
It is sufficient to take him to the responsible municipal office or to send him there by registered mail.
At the end of the year, driving licences issued between 1964 and 1993 become invalid.
However, drivers must gradually exchange other types of driving licences.
People with driving licences from 1994 to 2000 still have three years to exchange.
The validity of driving licences issued between 2001 and 2004 expires in December 2013.
According to Hanzelka, this is about 2.6 million more driving licences.
