The tool he used, a mini hockey bat, wrapped with isolator to prevent an electric shock on the solar panels that generate several hundred volts, had the astronauts on board the station invented and crafted.
When the action was finished, Scott Parazynski waited until the collector was fully folded before he counted his tools and returned to the station.
