Which insurance is best for me?
Car insurance covering a possible damage event caused by the driver involves a high cost, the amount of which again depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of production of the driver's licence, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even harder to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an policyholder.
This agreement shall be recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract which establishes that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and is obliged in return to submit the corresponding compensation in the event of a claim.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance which consists of several factors, including age, sex, time of drawing up the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that higher contributions are due in the event of a higher risk of accidents.
For this reason, both over 25-year-olds and women have to pay less contributions, because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, as they tend to have fewer accidents than single persons, according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the company's conviction.
The benefits attributed to the vehicle affect the frequency of driving and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
In drawing up the premium, insurance companies must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that suits his personal needs most.
At this point, we now list the most important points that should be considered when choosing an insurance policy in order to be able to make not only a performance but also a price-oriented choice.
The under 25-year-olds encounter numerous obstacles when choosing a low-cost insurance policy, such as low driving practice and a young driver's license.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to take out a full comprehensive insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a full insurance cover, so that the benefits of a full insurance cover, but are offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer must pay part of the amount incurred by the damage itself.
The amount is determined before the conclusion of the contract and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, Spain's main representative at First Europa, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is the extended insurance, which assures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused to his own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under 25 years old, it is in your hand to reduce the insurance costs; so your credit increases by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate of the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in the said tariff.
The amount of credits and penalties depends on the company and its income.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it can allow itself to increase the bonus payments, Noguera explains.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for the drivers to conclude a contract. This is due to the fact that the accident rate decreases with increasing driving practice.
Thus, it is most appropriate to opt for a full insurance with excess.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that most of the accidents occur in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginner has been removed.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married customer who has no children to take out full insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the corresponding person allows it.
On the part of the insurers, married couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate and, accordingly, their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, a full comprehensive insurance with excess interest (for an amount of 300 euros) would be the best option. In the event that you have received a high credit, an extended insurance policy that only applies for the third year of the vehicle is recommended.
Luis Noguera notes that they are more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power that allows them to make a higher contribution payment.
For pensioners, it is possible to take out a full insurance with excess insurance (for an amount of 150 euros) or an extended insurance, which only uses with a sufficiently high credit.
In the end, it is important to note that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver against possible accident damage, but also because it involves high costs, which require a thorough selection that corresponds to our personal situation.
