Two months ago, when the Prime Minister had withdrawn from the demand for an election, in a stupid way insulting the intelligence of the British by claiming that opinion polls had not influenced this decision, there was hope that he would offer a robust, efficient government.
Instead, as Vince Cable, the increasingly perceptive chairman of the Liberal Democrats, put it, the once feared Brown from Stalin has developed into Mr. Bean.
